oc:kn_2bdfa49e a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing YAML frontmatter for slash commands" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Frontmatter descriptions should be under 60 characters, start with a verb, and avoid redundant phrases like 'This command'. Valid model values are only sonnet, opus, or haiku." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Long descriptions break /help display formatting. Invalid model values cause command execution failures." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_819119df a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating a new slash command from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Follow the development workflow: design command purpose and arguments first, create the file with basic prompt, add minimal frontmatter (start with just description), test invocation, then refine with edge cases and comments." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incremental development catches issues early and avoids over-engineering commands before validating basic functionality." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_a3af67b9 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing and naming any slash command" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Follow single responsibility: one command should have one clear purpose. Use verb-noun naming (e.g., review-pr, fix-issue), always document arguments with argument-hint, and use the most restrictive allowed-tools possible." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Single-purpose commands are composable, testable, and discoverable. Minimal tool permissions reduce security surface. Clear naming and argument hints improve /help discoverability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a9df2ce0 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When navigating or teaching the command-development skill" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use progressive disclosure: start with SKILL.md core concepts, then load reference files (frontmatter-reference, plugin-features) and examples (simple-commands, plugin-commands) only as needed based on the specific task." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The skill is structured with ~2,470 words in SKILL.md for core concepts, ~13,500 words in references for detailed specs, and ~6,000 words in examples — loading everything upfront wastes tokens and overwhelms." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f0335a4b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any slash command prompt content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Write commands as instructions FOR Claude (agent consumption), not as messages TO the user. Direct Claude about what to do rather than describing what will happen." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Command content becomes Claude's instructions upon invocation. Writing for agent consumption ensures Claude acts correctly; writing for the user provides no actionable direction." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

